[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Automatically swaps to the right tool based on whatever your cursor (or right stick) is aimed at. No more pausing mid-rotation to scroll through your action bar.[/size]

[size=3][b]Targeting[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Cursor or right-stick aim[/b] — works for both mouse and controller, with a legacy proximity-based mode available if you'd rather it pick by what you're standing next to.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Tier-aware selection[/b] — when you've got multiple watering cans, hoes, or pickaxes on the bar, the highest-tier one wins.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Watering can logic[/b] — full cans are prioritised over empty ones; if everything's empty, the mod sends an empty can towards the nearest water source for refilling.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Tuning[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Per-tool toggles[/b] — every tool type can be individually enabled or disabled, so you can keep auto-swap on for hoes but off for the watering can.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Skip on farm tiles[/b] — optionally disable swapping while you're on your own farm, where you usually know exactly what tool you want.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Combat-aware[/b] — auto-swap turns itself off when enemies are nearby (range is configurable) so you don't accidentally pull out a hoe in a fight.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Switch cooldown[/b] — adjustable cooldown between swaps to stop the bar from flickering when your cursor sits on a boundary.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/7]UI Scales[/url] — finer control over the action bar and HUD makes the auto-swapped tool a lot easier to spot.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/37]Easy Living[/url] — a grab-bag of QoL tweaks that pairs naturally with this one.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/27]No Time For Fishing[/url] — once tools are sorted, skip the fishing minigame too.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/31]Keep Alive[/url] — required by this mod; keeps everything loaded between play sessions.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30][size=3]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/size][/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/31][size=3]Keep Alive[/size][/url]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[size=3]Built and tested against the latest Steam build of Sun Haven.[/size]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...\steamapps\common\Sun Haven\BepInEx\plugins[/code][/size]

